answers.body_markdown:
If you want only a True/False list, you can use a list comprehension:

    def kollaDublett(dataList):
        c = Counter(dataList)
        result = [True  if v &gt; 1 else False for x, v in c.items()]
        return result

Instead, to return a dictionary (expression:duplicate or not):

     def kollaDublett(dataList):
         c = Counter(dataList)
         result = {x:(True  if v &gt; 1 else False) for x, v in c.items()}
         return result

